    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "seen in Windows CI https://github.com/neovim/neovim/actions/runs/24906926058/job/72938580493?pr=35087\n\nthe `EBUSY: resource busy or locked` is different than https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39114 , which was closed by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39125 🤔 \n\n```\nNVIM_TEST_INTEG not set: skipping network integration test\nFAILED   2 tests, listed below:\nFAILED   ...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua @ 882: vim.pack add() startup works in plugin/\n...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:882: retry() attempts: 174\nExpected values to be equal.\nExpected:\ntrue\nActual:\nvim.NIL\n\nafter_each: [string \"?\"]:738: EBUSY: resource busy or locked: D:/a/neovim/neovim/build/Xtest_xdg_plugin/share/nvim-data/site/pack/core/opt/plugindirs\nstack traceback:\n\ttest/testutil.lua:88: in function 'retry'\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:882: in function 'assert_works'\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:908: in function <...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:904>\nFAILED   ...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua @ 912: vim.pack add() shows progress report during installation\nExpected values to be equal.\nExpected:\n4\nActual:\n5\nstack traceback:\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:321: in function 'assert_progress_report'\n\t...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:915: in function <...ld/Xtest_xdg_plugin/test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua:912>\n\n 5 SKIPPED TESTS\n 2 FAILED TESTS\n-------------------------\n```",
